Leaders from across the political divided were today united in supporting the ongoing war on corruption. President Uhuru Kenyatta, his deputy William Ruto and opposition leader Raila Odinga maintain there will be no relenting in the fight to stamp out the vice and added that more action will be coming in this front. They were speaking in separate functions. This came as 3 MPs called for the withdrawal of graft charges against agriculture PS Richard Lesiyampe.